Description: Ponemon Institute was founded in 2002 by Dr. Larry Ponemon.
Full Description: Ponemon Institute was founded in 2002 by Dr. Larry Ponemon. Headquartered in Michigan, Ponemon Institute is considered the pre-eminent research center dedicated to privacy, data protection and information security policy. Our annual consumer studies on privacy trust are widely quoted in the media and our research quantifying the cost of a data breach has become valuable to organizations seeking to understand the business impact of lost or stolen data.    Our research has made Ponemon Institute a thought leader on trends in corporate and government practices, consumer perceptions and potential cyber and insider threats that will affect the collection, management, and safeguarding of sensitive and confidential information. Our benchmark studies on privacy and data security practices provide guidance on how organizations can become better at building trust with their customers, employees, and business partners. We offer independent assurance and strategic advisory services to help companies enhance the effectiveness of their privacy and data protection programs and meet compliance and regulatory requirements in the United States and abroad.   Ponemon Institute is the parent organization of the Responsible Information Management Council. The RIM Council has members from leading multinational corporations and focuses on the development and execution of ethical principles for the collection and use of personal, sensitive, or confidential information. The RIM Council enables both seasoned privacy practitioners and those new to the profession to network and learn how to be as successful as possible in their organizations in both the private and public sectors.

Description: OMEBM is an established brand and retailer operating in North America.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: OMEBM is an established brand and retailer operating in North America.  OMEBM is a company that is privately held under the collective scope of affiliated companies privately owned and managed by OMEBM LLC. The first brand in its portfolio of brands was launched in 2012. The namesake band for the company offers a variety of premium high quality designer fashion jewelry, accessories, clothing, beauty products, and home accessories. OMEBM delivers a consistent customer experience through it's access to a broad network of vendor relationships and premium E-commerce platform.  OMEBM has offices located in New York, Texas, Utah, and Virginia, the primary headquarters for OMEBM are located in New York, New York. Launched in 2012 - the ever evolving style conscious company operates a diverse portfolio of retail brands; proving it's long term stability in the retail space by firmly rooting it's brands in adaptive e-commerce environments. After previously shuttering the brand to work on new developments and a reformatted user interface, the brand  announced a re-imagined version of the original store concept for the digital platform. Delivering on an established history of consistent results, exclusive first access was granted to retail industry insiders who provided feedback that the new platform was assured to bring significant success. In November 2019, OMEBM reopened it's digital doors to the public and feedback regarding the site redesign and offerings has been "overwhelmingly positive" - according to its leadership team responsible for the changes. In 2020 at the beginning of the COVID - 19 pandemic, Senior leadership at OMEBM declined to announce a concrete agenda for post pandemic retail developments. There was much speculation on the future of OMEBM and it's subsidiary brands. Industry analysts questioned if the previous projection for a transition into brick and mortar store fronts would yield true for OMEBM; or if the the parent company would continue to expand on the success of their digital footprint in light of overwhelming adverse conditions during the COVID-19 pandemic. OMEBM has been able to successfully manage it's exposure during an unprecedented retail disruption. As a privately held company, no financial data has been officially released. No IPO is slated for OMEBM at this time.  In 2021 the company announced sweeping changes to it's projected growth trajectory. Senior leadership at OMEBM have confirmed that the company will not expand into physical storefronts. Instead, the company plans to revamp its online presence with the launch of several new retail brands under its umbrella. As of 2023, the company has provided no statements on the scope of future business developments.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: CTM Insights is a research lab combined with an early stage technology studio and incubator, focused on new approaches to structural problems.  We provide seed funding and guidance to prototype ideas that can Change The Model (CTM) to some of the tech's hardest problems in Cyber Security.  Incubated ideas can result in IP licensing or as companies that continue on as independent entities. In addition to guidance and access to capital, CTM seeks to offer incubated ideas a set of shared services related to technology and market need validation, marketing, sales, go-to-market, beta customer capture, and conversion. Rather than a traditional venture capital focus on market clarity, CTM looks for clarity of a problem to be solved,  an understanding of why current approaches are unlikely to meet the need, and a fundamentally new approach. CTM was founded in 2017 by Lou Steinberg, a serial entrepreneur and corporate executive.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: All animals are, physically speaking, beings of light. The Zoological Lighting Institute (ZLI)  maintains a charitable mission to support the sciences of light and life through the arts for animal welfare and wildlife conservation purposes; both of which are crucial for community and individual well-being. We are a humanitarian animal welfare group, pursuing United Nations Sustainable Design Goals (SDGs), by raising awareness and funds for the all important arena of APPLIED PHOTOBIOLOGY. ZLI offers 1) grants and endowment opportunities, 2) franchised animal welfare station investment, 3) mindful animal welfare design programs (fashion, architecture, product), 4) 'PhotoDiversity Films' media production, (including anime series curation and educational documentaries dedicated to the sciences of light and life), as well as corporate sponsorship of IDEA (Inclusion, Diversity, Engagement, Access) driven programming to build networks appropriately for our mission. TO DEMONSTRATE THE VALUE of applied photobiology, ZLI organizes its initiatives into ZLI Campaigns.  These include mental health (ZLI's Bearanoia Campaign), anti-Asian hate mitigation (underscoring accommodation and adaptability in ZLI's Beached Campaign), reproductive / women's health (ZLI's Healthy Glow Campaign), food security (ZLI's Insect Apocalypse Campaign), healthy aging (ZLI's Otohime's Time Campaign), and migration/border challenges (ZLI's Save a Billion Birds! Campaign). Each ZLI Campaign offers its own 1) Grants/Endowments, 2) Monitoring Protocols, 3) Design Emphasis, 4) Anime Film Series, and 5) IDEA Programming, such as ZLI's Save a Billion Birds! Biking for Birds Programs and ZLI's Bearanoia Campaign sponsored エゾヒグマ (Ezo Higuma) Anti-Bullying Baseball Camps featuring baseball legend Carlos Mirabal.
